values: I've been feeling great all week. I don't know what it is exactly, but I've been feeling like happy and normal. It sucks that this couldn't come sooner, because now I finally feel all social and I miss people and want to hang out with them. But I'm kind of scared that I'm coming down off this high, whatever it is, back into the moody funk I was in before. I don't really think I'm bipolar, because I'm not really manic or feeling super energetic. I think I'd rather not be, because then this feeling wouldn't have to be out of the ordinary. It would be like when you appreciate being able to breathe after being sick for a while. Maybe I should see a psychiatrist about getting some anti-depressants up in this bitch. Hm, this post didn't turn out so happy. Hopefully I feel better again tomorrow. I think I'm just worried about my Art History quiz. But whee...3 day weekend after that.

If I was a rockstar I would request a bowl of lime skittles. I was thinking this last night. I've been having a stupid hard time getting to sleep lately, and I really need to have a good night's sleep for my Religious Studies final on Thursday morning. I need to do something to tire myself out I guess.

     I'm being such a whiny bitch to myself about writing my final essay for English. I keep procrastinating and refreshing ONTD like constantly. Argh I'm getting there though...1.5 pages down. That crappy stick figure drawing that goes "Ffffuuuuuu" cracks me up so much. That's what I've been like for the past 4 hours though :P

Lisa had a conversation with them :)

Gym Class Heroes rocked. The lead singer was really funny.
Of course.. Hellogoodbye was amazing and I loved every minute. Dashboard Confessional....wow. I never listened that much to it before. Dude can really sing. Jack's Mannequin was awesome too, but we were about ready to pass out in the mosh pit, so we left. The mosh pit was insane; people were all pushing and Mandy and I fell. It was pretty scary. There were people all up in my business and like...grinding..against..me..    :(

To be in the mosh pit, you need to be ready to be like "FUCK OFF, BITCH!!" when a bitch is elbowing everyone. That's what Tiff did lol.
It's also really hot and hard to breathe, but the minute the band started to play, it was like....everything goes away. You're just so excited.  ^^

*sigh*. I'm so wiped out...
We definitely need to do this again.
Yes. most def.

My dad started looking at me kinda funny for a while when we were having lunch the other day. Then he said that I had my mom's face shape and her nose. Huh. I guess I kinda do, or I just don't look like my dad very much. But I think I'm totally more like my dad. 

A lot of times when my mom is trying to be funny, or just in general I guess, she kind of annoys me. My dad only annoys me when he's being unreasonable and has a temper. So anyway, when I went to San Francisco with my parents, on the ride over there, my dad totally Punk'd my mom. He took her purse from her seat and waited till she noticed, and she started getting scared that she'd left it at the last stop. Then I started laughing and he took it out. It was pretty funny. 

Also, one time my dad tried to sing Hips Don't Lie.
One time my mom tried to sing Gasolina.
so yeah. not related to her.

does everyone feel like this? or is this thing just freakily correct..i mean..for a color quiz..

Existing Situation

      Is seeking a solution to existing problems or anxieties, but is liable to find it difficult to decide on a right course to follow.

Stress Sources

      Is responsive to outside stimuli and wants to experience everything intensely, but is finding the existing situation extremely frustrating. Needs sympathetic understanding and a sense of security. Distressed by her apparently powerlessness to achieve her goals.


Restrained Characteristics

      Feels trapped in a distressing or uncomfortable situation and seeking some way of gaining relief. 

      Feels that things stand in her way, that circumstances are forcing her to compromise and forgo some pleasures for the time being.


Desired Objective

      Wants to make a favorable impression and be recognized. Needs to feel appreciated and admired. Sensitive and easily hurt if no notice is taken of her or if she is not given adequate acknowledgment.


Actual Problem

      Works to strengthen her position and bolster her self-esteem by examining her own accomplishments (and those of others) with critical appraisal and scientific discrimination. Insists on having things clear-cut and unequivocal.

Actual Problem #2

      Depleted vitality has created an intolerance for any further stimulation, or demands on her resources. This sense of powerlessness, combined with frustration that she cannot control events, subjects her to agitation, irritation, and acute distress. She tries to escape these by stubborn insistence on her own point of view, but the general condition of helplessness renders this often unsuccessful. Is therefore very sensitive to criticism and quick to take offense.
